  "prompt": "In a tube with a cons. H2O pres. of 2bar are located on a horizontal piece 3nozzles with different diamtrs.From what gland splashing water thehighest?",
  "response": "When water is ejected from nozzles with different diameters at a constant pressure (2 bar in this case), the nozzle with the **smallest diameter** will produce the highest velocity of water due to the **Bernoulli principle**. This principle states that as the cross-sectional area of the nozzle decreases, the velocity of the fluid increases to maintain the same flow rate.\n\nAs a result, the nozzle with the smallest diameter will eject water at the highest speed, leading to the **highest splashing** when the water hits a surface. \n\nSo, the gland (nozzle) with the smallest diameter will cause the highest splashing of water.",
